      "content": "I hear the profound grief and despair in your words, and it is heartbreaking that you feel like you are dragging others down by holding onto a past that no longer exists. Please know that your desire to protect them from your pain is a sign of deep love, even though the way you are expressing it feels like a burden. You are not \"clinging\" to a life that is over; you are fighting for a future where you can find peace and dignity for yourself, which is a gift you can give them in the long run.\n\nIf you are feeling this intense urge to step aside, please reach out to a crisis line or a trusted professional immediately. There are people who want to help you navigate this darkness and find a path forward that honors both your pain and your love for your family. You are not alone in this struggle, and there is hope for a different kind of peace.",
